Advanced Student Performance Management System
System Documentation
________________________________________
1. Project Overview
The Advanced Student Performance Management System is a Java-based application designed to help universities efficiently manage and monitor student academic performance.
The system tracks students, courses, grades, GPA calculations, and attendance records. Additionally, it provides automated alerts for students with low attendance, supporting early academic intervention.
By automating academic processes, the system reduces manual workload, improves data accuracy, and ensures secure access to performance information for both students and faculty members.
________________________________________
2. Project Objectives
The main objectives of this system are as follows:
•	Automate GPA calculation and academic performance tracking
•	Maintain accurate attendance records and generate alerts for low attendance
•	Provide role-based access control for students and faculty
•	Integrate a secure database system for storing academic data
•	Apply Object-Oriented Programming (OOP) principles for clean, maintainable, and scalable code
________________________________________
3. Technologies Used
The system is implemented using the following technologies:
•	Programming Language: Java
•	Database Management System: Microsoft SQL Server
•	Database Connectivity: JDBC (Java Database Connectivity)
•	Design Paradigm: Object-Oriented Programming (OOP)
•	Architecture Pattern: DAO (Data Access Object)
________________________________________
4. System Users and Roles
The system supports multiple user roles, each with specific permissions.
4.1 Students
Students can:
•	View their personal academic information
•	Calculate and view GPA
•	Check attendance percentage
•	Receive alerts when attendance falls below 75%
4.2 Faculty
Faculty members can:
•	Enter and update student grades
•	Define assessments and deadlines
•	View detailed student performance reports
4.3 Admin (Conceptual Role)
The admin role is responsible for:
•	Managing users, courses, and enrollments
•	Controlling and maintaining system data
